The paper focuses on a longitudinal study of smartphone usage, specifically the iPhone 3GS, and its impact on users. The study includes structured interviews and in-device logging, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social informatics (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the influence of socioeconomic status (SES) on usage, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or computational social science (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses application and web usage dynamics, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
